title="The Octonions">[baez-2002-octonions]</fr:link></fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>We define an <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Ideal</html:dfn> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(J,\circ )]]></fr:tex> to be a subspace <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B\subseteq  J]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b\in  B]]></fr:tex> implies <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\circ  b\in  B]]></fr:tex> for every <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  J]]></fr:tex>. This generalizes the familiar notion of an ideal from rings (and things).</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
